# Tailwind v4

- Prefer Tailwind utilities; avoid custom CSS unless necessary.
- Use theme tokens defined via `@theme` in CSS; avoid hardcoded arbitrary values when a token exists.
- For conditional classes, use the repo's existing helper (e.g. `cn()` / `clsx()`), don't invent a new one.

## v4 specifics

- Do not add or reference `tailwind.config.*` (v4 config lives in CSS via `@theme`).
- Do not add `content` config; content detection is automatic.
- Use `@import "tailwindcss"` instead of `@tailwind base/components/utilities`.
